flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Detection of potential quality issues through PFMEA, Control Plan, MSA, Quality Gates, and Deviation/Non-Conformance processes.]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers - Ingest PFMEA outcomes, control plan parameters, MSA results, and quality gate statuses.]
  N1 --> N2[Cortex: Cortex Auto Forecast - Analyze PFMEA outcomes and control plan parameters to predict potential quality issues.]
  N2 --> N3[Cortex: Data Quality & Validation - Integrate MSA results and evaluate measurement uncertainty.]
  N3 --> N4{PB: CWB Lifecycle - Set up and enforce quality gates based on analysis results.}
  N4 -->|Primary| N5{PB: CWB Lifecycle - Design and implement processes for handling quality deviations and non-conformances.}
  N5 --> N6[PB: Notification - Notify relevant stakeholders about quality issues and recommended actions.]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Improved first-pass yields, reduced scrap and rework, lower warranty costs, and enhanced on-time delivery performance.]
  N4 -->|High measurement uncertainty detected| B1[Trigger corrective actions and re-evaluate MSA results.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Ensures measurement reliability and reduces false positives.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Quality gate fails| B2[Initiate rework or scrap process.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Minimizes defects and optimizes throughput.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Significant deviation detected| B3[Escalate to supplier or initiate containment and rework.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Balances cost and delivery impact while ensuring quality.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]